<item>
            <title>[SPARK-47839] Fix Aggregate bug in RewriteWithExpression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-47839</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following query will fail:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-sql&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;NULLIF&lt;/span&gt;(id + 1, 1)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;range&lt;/span&gt;(10)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;group&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; id
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because &lt;tt&gt;NullIf&lt;/tt&gt; gets rewritten to &lt;tt&gt;With&lt;/tt&gt;, then &lt;tt&gt;RewriteWithExpression&lt;/tt&gt; tries to pull common expression &lt;tt&gt;id + 1&lt;/tt&gt; out of the aggregate, resulting in an invalid plan.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
